Kelly Clarkson's first single from 4th album All I Ever Wanted out March 10th 2009.  On January 28th, 2009 Billboard announced the single leaped 96 spots to land at #1 in its second week on the Hot 100 chart, beating Britney Spears' record by just one to become Kelly's second #1 single, her first since &quot;A Moment Like This.&quot;

 This was written by Dr. Luke and Max Martin and Claude Kelly. According to the <a href="http://www.songfacts.com/detail.php?id=14192" rel="nofollow">My Life Would Suck Without You Songfacts</a>, Martin had &quot;an idea of some of the concepts.&quot; He and Dr Luke came up with the music, then Martin threw some ideas at Kelly, who then came up with the lyrics. 


